eference>ES/G005613/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>This Post Doctoral Fellowship (PDF) award is aimed at assisting the researcher to disseminate his PhD research which uses the Free Compulsory Universal Basic Education (fCUBE) policy in Ghana as an exemplar and the composite theory conceptualisation of policy as 'text' and 'discourse' as a theoretical approach to explore the apparent disjuncture between policy intentions and purposes in theory and outcomes in practice. In particular, this grant is intended to serve as a platform for the dissemination of the findings of this research through publications, conference presentations and user-engagement activities, especially with Ghanaian stakeholders, and with the view to deepening understanding of policy implementation processes in low-income countries. The award also aims at promoting the use of critical discourse analysis (CDA) as an inter-disciplinary analytical tool among policy practitioners and students of policy sociology in Sub-Saharan Africa. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>A significant remit of this award concerns the researcher's skills development to support his future job applications. In this regards, the researcher will work closely with the Research Programme Consortium on Implementing Education Quality in Low-in come Countries (EdQual), in his host institution, with the view to developing a research proposal for an ESRC First Grant funded collaborative research at the end of the PDF year.&lt;/p>

